se. It also includes collecting indigenous knowledge to help in discovering and exploiting genetic or biochemical resources. While it is a high risk area for investors, it can have massive returns. Of the world\u2019s 25 top-selling pharmaceuticals, 10 were originally sourced from animals, plants or micro-organ- isms. See Australian Museum Online, http://www.amonline.net.au/factsheets/bioprospecting.htm; Wikipedia, http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bioprospecting 9The Convention on", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "c0becdff-cb81-466e-945e-aed3defd79d0": {"__data__": {"id_": "c0becdff-cb81-466e-945e-aed3defd79d0", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/gender-dimensions-intellectual-property-and-traditional-medicinal-knowledge", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "Gender Dimensions of Intellectual Property and Traditional Medicinal Knowledge", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/gender-dimensions-intellectual-property-and-traditional-medicinal-knowledge", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "9f2f428106b15db0868368e5217fe9f91fdbb0340ff6c15bfedf8d6d6ea72885"}, "3": {"node_id": "acf2a70e-ef53-454e-ad46-c676e8d4f066", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/gender-dimensions-intellectual-property-and-traditional-medicinal-knowledge", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "a80b420259a3b8a1b6b72b8500